1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on the performance of a pretrained BERT model on the task of propaganda analysis at sentence level, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of BERT, a state-of-the-art language model, for propaganda analysis can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper involves fine-tuning a pretrained BERT model on a specific task, which is a common technique in machine learning. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - BERT is a neural network-based language model, and the paper discusses its performance on a specific task, which can be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing community. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves analyzing text data to identify propaganda techniques, which can be considered as a form of information retrieval.
